 Transfer and Accumulation System  standards  Documentation  Dr  Martin Nassua of HSU is the point of contact for foreign students  He approves the transcripts of courses that you take and sends them to Colonel Sunnen so that they can be translated for the VMI Registrar s Office  Courses in German for Foreigners  Cadets have had the opportunity to take courses at the Sprachenzentrum  language center  at the UniBw in order to help with their German language skills  This is well worth inquring about  You may also have the opportunity to teach English  either formally or informally  Col  Sunnen Home Courses Instructional Bundeswehr Exchange Conference Papers Foreign Links VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 